          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2011-11-10 00:20:04.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-769 ptlrpc: Do not miss pending signals in ptlrpc_set wait",
        "message": "LU-769 ptlrpc: Do not miss pending signals in ptlrpc_set wait\n\nconf_sanity test 23a highlighted a problem in ptlrpc_set_wait logic,\nif we enter there with a signal pending and the import is not FULL,\nthere is no way to interrupt such a set because we block signals\nall the time. Enabling signals all the time is not an option either.\nWaiting until import reconnects is questionable too since it might\nnever come up after all (like in the test 23a).\nSo for the solution we will just manually mark the set as interrupted\nafter the initial wait.\n\nChange-Id: Iaa3e356e971b4f75fd7f21cc579c85f7487719a0\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
